# SpectraBreast — MASt3R-SfM + ArUco

`SpectraBreast` turns a folder of RGB images into a metric fused point cloud, with ArUco markers in **2D** (per-image JSON + annotations) and **3D** (`aruco_markers_3d.json` after alignment). **Camera poses and intrinsics are optional**: omit them to rely on MASt3R-SfM and ArUco for scale; add `pose_dir` and `camera_params_dir` when you have ground-truth calibration.

## Install (with [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/))

Clone-to-run:

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url> SpectraBreast-Vision
cd SpectraBreast-Vision
uv sync
uv run spectra --help
```

This project is now fully managed by `uv`:

- Dependencies are declared in `pyproject.toml` (including local editable `mast3r/asmk` via `tool.uv.sources`).
- The CLI entrypoint is declared in `project.scripts`.
- You can run commands without manual activation via `uv run ...`.

If you prefer activating a shell:

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate
spectra --help
```

## CLI commands

- `spectra run` - main pipeline (`MASt3R-SfM -> fuse -> ArUco align -> exports`)
- `spectra reconstruct` - hidden backward-compatible alias of `run`
- `spectra detect` - 2D ArUco only (no SfM / no 3D triangulation)
- `spectra viewer` - Gradio browser to inspect outputs under `RESULTS/`
- `spectra tui` - hidden Textual app for interactive launching (optional dependency)
- `spectra calibrate-intrinsics` - checkerboard-based camera intrinsic calibration

```bash
# Config-driven
uv run spectra run --config configs/default.yaml

# Overrides
uv run spectra run -c configs/default.yaml --rgb-dir DATA/s/rgb --out RESULTS --run-name trial1

# Optional GT: same stem order as images → pose_*.txt + intrinsics.npy folder
uv run spectra run -c configs/default.yaml \
  --rgb-dir DATA/s/rgb --pose-dir DATA/s/poses --camera-params-dir DATA/s/cam

# 2D detection only
uv run spectra detect DATA/s/rgb /tmp/aruco_out

# Intrinsic calibration from checkerboard images
uv run spectra calibrate-intrinsics --image-dir checkerboard --output-dir intrinsics

# Arbitrary YAML field
uv run spectra run -c configs/default.yaml -s mast3r.voxel_size=0.002
```

## Callable modules and entry points

Install once with:

```bash
uv sync
```

Then you can invoke the same functionality through these module/CLI entry points:

```bash
# Preferred packaged CLI entry point
uv run spectra --help

# Equivalent module entry point (same Typer app/commands)
uv run python -m spectra --help

# Direct module call to the Typer app implementation
uv run python -m spectra.cli --help

# Direct callable Python module functions (without CLI wrappers)
uv run python -c "from pathlib import Path; from spectra.viewer import run_viewer; run_viewer(results_dir=Path('RESULTS'))"
uv run python -c "from pathlib import Path; from spectra.tui import run_tui; run_tui(config_path=Path('configs/default.yaml'), data_root=Path('DATA'))"

# Legacy argparse shim kept for old scripts
uv run python mast3r_pipeline.py --help
```

Notes:

- `uv run spectra`, `uv run python -m spectra`, and `uv run python -m spectra.cli` expose the same command tree (`run`, `detect`, `viewer`, hidden aliases).
- `spectra viewer` / `spectra tui` are the CLI wrappers around `spectra.viewer.run_viewer` and `spectra.tui.run_tui`.
- `spectra calibrate-intrinsics` wraps `spectra.calibration.calibrate_intrinsics`.
- `mast3r_pipeline.py` is backward compatibility only; prefer `spectra run`.

## Input layout

```
DATA/myset/
  rgb/              # required: *.jpg / *.png
  poses/            # optional: pose_0000.txt … (one line: X Y Z R P Y)
  camera_parameters/  # optional: intrinsics.npy (3×3), camera2ee.npy (ignored by fusion)
```

Relative paths in YAML are resolved from the current working directory.

## Outputs (per run folder under `output.root` / `run_name` or timestamp)

- `cloud.ply`, `cloud.npz` — fused RGB point cloud  
- `aruco_detections/json/`, `annotated/` — 2D ArUco  
- `aruco_markers_3d.json` — 3D marker corners in the output frame (when alignment succeeds)  
- `reconstruction_metadata.json` — run summary  
- `run.yaml` / `run.json` — resolved configuration  
- `rerun/spectra.rrd` — optional Rerun recording (if enabled)

## Python API

```python
from spectra import load_config, run_reconstruction

cfg = load_config("configs/default.yaml")
result = run_reconstruction(cfg)   # result.run_dir, result.cloud_points, …
```

Programmatic `ReconstructionConfig` uses `InputConfig`, `Mast3rConfig`, `ArucoConfig`, `SurfaceConfig`, `RerunConfig` (see `spectra/config.py`).

## Legacy shims

- `mast3r_pipeline.py` — old argparse entry; prefer `spectra run`.
- `intrinsic_calibration.py` — old script shim; prefer `spectra calibrate-intrinsics`.
- `helpers.py` — backward-compatible shim; internals now use `spectra.transforms`.

## Repository layout (high level)

- `configs/default.yaml` — main knob set for MASt3R-SfM + ArUco + surface + Rerun  
- `spectra/` — package: pipeline, `mast3r` backend, ArUco, surface, I/O  
- `mast3r/` — vendored / submodule MASt3R (see project setup)  

`vggt/` may remain in the tree for other experiments; the **unified pipeline no longer calls VGGT**.
